  "commentary": "With SPX at 6818.74 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6810 (-57.3B) and positive gamma ceiling at 6830 (+31.5B), dealers are caught in a violent hedging zone where they're forced to buy any dip toward 6810 and sell any rally toward 6830. The -52.5% 1-minute move followed by +41.1% 5-minute swing perfectly illustrates the amplifying nature of this negative gamma regime, with dealers mechanically chasing price in both directions. Watch for continued whipsaw action between these 6810-6830 boundaries, with any sustained break below 6810 likely triggering accelerated dealer buying into the deeper negative gamma walls at 6815/6800/6805.\n\nBottom line: expect violent swings between 6810 and 6830 as dealers amplify every move.",
